  native genomic sequence. This is achieved by introducing double-stranded DNA
  breaks in the host genome using gene editing tools, such as CRISPR/Cas9 or  
  TALENS, together with template DNA (often a corrected or modified version of
  the gene) flanked by homology arms to promote the sequence incorporation    
  into the host&apos;s genome at a native locus by means of homology-directed 
  repair.</obo:IAO_0000115>                                                   
